Usage : look [at <item>]
        examine <item>

Look is the command you use to get information on the things around you.
Look on its own gives you the description of your current location.  If you
type look at something, you will get an in depth description of that item.
If there is a more detailed description of that item, you can get it by using
examine item.  Usually however the look at item and examine item will be the
same.

Examples:

look
look at shadow
look at second sword
look at head of troll
examine head of troll
